name: Advanced Personality Psychology
description: This course is intended to advance students' understanding of contemporary personality theory and research. Emerging challenges and controversies in the areas of personality structure, dynamics, and development will be discussed.
prerequisites: [PSYB07H3 or STAB22H3 or STAB23H3] and PSYB30H3 and [an additional 0.5 credit at the B-level in PSY courses]
